caption: It was a bit overpriced for my liking, no rice bowl should cost $16, but the food was great. I ordered for my family and had high expectations. It's a great concept as a restaurant.  I was highly disappointed the fried chicken taste like the pre made fried chicken at shoprite or Walmart. The Mac and cheese ramen had too much going on with a sweet taste. The tater tots were just that tater tots..nothing special. The veggies I'm not going to lie I threw them away didn't even taste it or want to feed it to my kid.

Would of gave two stars, but after eating the wings (Gangnam Style) I've been running to the restroom ( the only item I feel was ok in flavor). What made me write this is the dry, burnt grease tasting chicken. I could not take more the 2 bites before I felt overwhelmed. I will add this was the first time this year I had fried chicken, if that means anything. don't let the flash fool you, the chicken is Cajun black.

Great spot off of Franklin for delicious food. There are two booths for outdoor seating, one of which has a heat lamp. The entire space felt very covid friendly. Service is always slow, so make sure you have lots of time and grab a beer while you wait. Highly recommend the tater tots and ramen & cheese.

Awesome .Very helpful staff,i hightly recomend.  Pleasantly surprised by how great this little take out breakfast sandwich spot it. Do yourself a favor and check it out!
Not good.
Food was cold and overpriced. Owner seems rude and confrontational when this was pointed out to him. Will be telling friends and family to go somewhere else.

Okay so I live down the block, like literally the same block just a couple of buildings down and decided to try this for the first time and it would be just my luck to find a nice hair in my food. To be completely honest the only reason they even have one star is because I ate the fried chicken bun first before I saw the hair and it was delicious. The hair was in the pulled pork bun, which was so disappointing.  Edit: I called and they refunded my money.
Fastest pickup experience that I have had in a long time. Thank you Memphis Seoul.

Me and my friends went to Memphis Seoul for restaurant week. Upon arriving we looked at the menu and couldn’t decide what to get. One of my friends did not order anything she said she did not like the way it looked. I ordered the meat loaf, ramen Mac and cheese and mixed veggie. While riding in my friends car back home we noticed a foul order. My friend closed the window thinking the smell was from outside. I was dropped off to my car and while driving I noticed the same smell. That’s when I realized it was the food. The  meatloaf was two big very salty pierces. They were frozen before it was cooked and the veggie was cold. The ramen Mac and cheese had no flavor and the Mac and cheese and veggies portions was small. I called Memphis Seoul to see if I can get a refund or exchange it for something else. I spoke with a guy named Richard.I explained the situation to him .I told him that if he doesn’t resolve it I will write a review. He placed me on hold to speak with the owner. I overheard the owner yelling saying that he doesn’t care about what I said about the portion and the food and he doesn’t care if I write a bad review. The owner got on the phone and was extremely rude he said he doesn’t offer refunds. I asked if I can exchange it for something else. He said he’s not doing anything for me since I said I was going to write a review. He said he doesn’t care if I write a review. I would not recommend anyone going to Memphis Seoul if you are unhappy with your over priced food you can’t even complain. The owner doesn’t want to hear it or he isn’t sympathetic to it issue.

So, they we're super busy because of restaurant week, but even though there was a delay in receiving our food, it was crazy good. Ribs fell off the bone, cornbread was moist, jackfruit Sammie was great, loaded tots were delicious. Will definitely order here again.

Probably the best cornbread I’ve ever had in my entire life. Ramen Mac n cheese was amazing. The ribs were amazing. Fried chicken was a bit dry, but they delivered it really far so that’s understandable l. The cole slaw wasn’t great. We did literally drive half an hour the day after ordering to pick up more cornbread and ramen Mac n cheese though. It was that good. Can’t wait to try the bulgogi meatloaf.

My hopes were quite high for this place as combining two of my favorite foods had me salivating. Sadly, the fried chicken was hard as a catchers mitt, was covered in about 2 inches of batter, and had about the same taste as wood shavings on a shop floor- Absolutely tasteless. Adding insult to the letdown, the cornbread was about as dry as a bean counter’s humor, and that’s being generous. My apologies to bean counters.

Great nook, with solid comfort food. Negative is that there are inconsistencies with the recipes changing, and each time I've been, the food takes a long time to get, for it being quick service. Plan to wait more than 20 minutes for one platter if you order in.

It was my first time coming here and I cannot say when I will be back. I ordered several items off the menu, but here are the 2 highlights that I think sum up my experience.  The ramen n' cheese: as someone who's spent their childhood growing up in the south and a lover of korean spices I was expecting a combination of both flavor profiles, but it just wasn't there. Instead it was the seasonings you would put on baked mac & cheese and put into ramen. There was memphis flavor that was to be expected, but the "Seoul" was nowhere to be found.  Strawberry Soju Cake: this one is iffy and totally dependent on what type of sweet tooth you have. At times I want my dessert to be super sweet and other times not so much. Luckily this cake came on a day where I wanted my dessert to be super sweet. The strawberry flavor could be tasted in both the cake and icing, and although someone might think that this might be too much strawberry it's not. One thing that was missed was the soju flavor. Maybe it was taken out within the cooking process, but I wasn't able to detect it. Also the icing is thick, think of fondant but more manageable.  Overall the experience did not match up to my expectations, but that doesn't mean that all hope is lost. Hopefully in the future I will be able to taste more the of the "Seoul" in my food.
